description: This poem focuses on Sartre's concept of "The Look" - the state of reflective self-consciousness as conditioned by the recognition of the other's conscious experience and the never-ending sense that this is what makes us truly alone. It also pays homage to Cher, whose music I do not care for, but who seems to have struggled well with celebrity in the face of constant criticism from withered and jealous persons. Because they both arose in the Greatest Century, there are 20 editions.
